('Attention Alignment Between Humans and Vision-Language Models', 'Isaac R. Christian, Udith Haputhanthrige, Hanna Hornfeld, Declan Campbell, Samuel Nastase, Taylor Webb, Michael Graziano', '2026', 'Visual perception depends on top-down goals and bottom-up sensory mechanisms. Vision-language models implement both, allowing us to treat each component as a separable hypothesis about what drives where we look. We compared spatial attention maps from six vision-language models against human fixatio', 'https://arxiv.org/pdf/2606.17410v1', '0', 'arXiv', 'cs.CV', 'Vision Transformer', datetime('now')),
('Adaptive inference and function vectors in deep transformers', 'Ravin Raj, Gautam Reddy', '2026', 'Transformers are widely used as a general-purpose substrate for learning complex correlations between a large collection of coupled variables, but their internal mechanisms have remained mysterious. We introduce a theory of a deep transformer as a mean-field interacting system that implements distri', 'https://arxiv.org/pdf/2606.16694v1', '0', 'arXiv', 'cs.LG, cs.AI, physics.app-ph, q-bio.NC', 'Self-Attention', datetime('now')),
('Scaling Short-Term Memory of Visuomotor Policies for Long-Horizon Tasks', 'Rutav Shah, Rajat Kumar Jenamani, Xiaohan Zhang, Lingfeng Sun, Roberto Martín-Martín, Yuke Zhu, Deva Ramanan, Karl Schmeckpeper', '2026', 'Many robotic tasks require short-term memory, whether it''s retrieving an object that''s no longer visible or turning off an appliance after a set period. Yet, most visuomotor policies trained via imitation learning rely only on immediate sensory input without using past experiences to guide decisions', 'https://arxiv.org/pdf/2606.16178v1', '0', 'arXiv', 'cs.RO', 'Self-Attention', datetime('now')),
